#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Server Requirements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:4
msgid ""
"FreshRSS is a web application. This means you’ll need a web server to run "
"it. FreshRSS requirements are really low, so it should run on most shared "
"host servers, or any old computer you happen to have on hand."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:6
msgid ""
"You need to verify that your server can run FreshRSS before installing it. "
"If your server has the proper requirements and FreshRSS does not work, "
"please contact us to find a solution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Software      | Recommended             | Also Works With         |\n"
"| ------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------- |\n"
"| Web server    | **Apache 2**            | Nginx                   |\n"
"| PHP           | **PHP 7+**              | PHP 5.6+                |\n"
"| PHP modules   | Required: libxml, cURL, JSON, PDO\\_MySQL, PCRE and ctype."
" <br>Required (32-bit only): GMP <br> Recommanded: Zlib, mbstring, iconv,"
" ZipArchive <br> *For the whole modules list see"
" [Dockerfile](https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/blob/master/Docker/Dockerfi"
"le-Alpine#L7-L9)* | |\n"
"| Database      | **MySQL 5.5.3+**        | SQLite 3.7.4+, PostgreSQL 9.5+   "
"       |\n"
"| Browser       | **Firefox**             | Chrome, Opera, Safari, or"
" IE11/Edge[^1] |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting the appropriate version of FreshRSS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:19
msgid ""
"FreshRSS has three different releases or branches. Each branch has its own "
"release frequency. So it is better if you spend some time to understand the "
"purpose of each release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Stable release"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:23
msgid "[Download](https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/archive/master.zip)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:25
msgid ""
"This version is really stable, tested thoroughly, and you should not face "
"any major bugs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:27
msgid ""
"Stable releases are not released on a set schedule. Rather, they are "
"released whenever we consider that our goal for new features is reached, and "
"the software is stable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:29
msgid ""
"It could happen that we make two releases in a short span of time if we have "
"a really good coding pace. In reality, we are all working on the project in "
"our spare time, so a new release usually occurs every few months."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Development version"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:33
msgid "[Download](https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/archive/dev.zip)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:35
msgid ""
"As its name suggests, the development version is the working codebase, "
"intended for developers. **This release may be unstable!**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:37
msgid ""
"If you want to keep track of the most recent enhancements or help the "
"developers with bug reports, this is the branch for you. If you use this "
"version, please keep in mind that you need to follow the branch activity on "
"Github (via [the branch RSS feed](https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/"
"commits/dev.atom), for instance), and manually pull new commits."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:39
msgid ""
"Some say that the main developers use this branch on a daily basis without "
"problem. They may know what they are doing…"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/02_Prerequisites.md:40
msgid ""
"[^1]: IE11/Edge may not support all features found in FreshRSS on other "
"browsers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "General Installation Instructions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:4
msgid ""
"These instructions are intended as general guidelines for installing "
"FreshRSS. You may wish to consult the [Step-by-step Tutorial for installing "
"FreshRSS on Debian 9/Ubuntu 16.04](06_LinuxInstall.md) if you don't "
"currently have a web server and don't have experience setting one up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:6
msgid ""
"Before you begin, make sure that you've read the [prerequisites]"
"(02_Prerequisites.md) for running FreshRSS. As shorthand, `.` refers to the "
"directory to which your FreshRSS installation lives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:8
msgid ""
"If the computer you're running on is not currently running a web server, "
"you'll first need to install and configure a web server, a version of PHP, "
"and an appropriate database, as listed in the prerequisites. [Example Apache "
"and Nginx configuration files can be found here](10_ServerConfig.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:10
msgid ""
"Download your chosen version of FreshRSS, or fetch it via git. It's "
"advisable that you put FreshRSS in `/usr/share/`, and symlink the `./p/` "
"folder to the root of your web server.[^1]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:12
msgid ""
"Give ownership of the FreshRSS folder to your web server user (often `www-"
"data`). Give group read permissions to all files in `.`[^2], and group write "
"permissions to `./data/`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:14
msgid "Install needed PHP modules."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:16
msgid ""
"Create a database for FreshRSS to use. Note the username and password for "
"this database, as it will be needed during installation!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '6. '
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:18
msgid ""
"Using your supported web browser of choice, navigate to the address you've "
"installed your server to complete the installation from the GUI.[^3]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:20
msgid ""
"[^1]: Make sure to expose only the `./p/` folder to the Web, as the other "
"directories contain personal and sensitive data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:22
msgid ""
"[^2]: If you wish to allow updates from the web interface, also give group "
"write permissions to this folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/03_Installation.md:23
msgid ""
"[^3]: Assuming your server is `http://example.net`, this address could be "
"`http://example.net/p/` if you didn't follow our previous advice about not "
"exposing the `./p/` folder."
msgstr ""

