#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Promoting a user to admin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:9
msgid ""
"At the moment, there can be only one *admin* user for the system.  Thus "
"promoting one user to *admin* demotes the current *admin* user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:12
msgid ""
"The recommended way of promoting a user is with the help of the CLI tool.  "
"You only have to do is to run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Code fence info string
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:12
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:19
#: en/./users/06_Fever_API.md:68 en/./users/06_Fever_API.md:74
#: en/./users/06_Mobile_access.md:69
#: en/./users/07_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:43
#: en/./users/07_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "sh"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"./cli/reconfigure.php --default_user <username>\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:19
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can edit configuration files manually.  To do so, you "
"need to change the *default_user* value in the file *./data/config.php*.  As "
"the file is a PHP file, you have to make sure that it's still valid after "
"the update by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"php -l ./data/config.php\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Disabling self-registration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/04_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Users can register directly on the login screen only if the configuration"
" allows them.\n"
"Under *Administration* > *System configuration*, you have access to *Max"
" number of accounts*.\n"
"As stated on that page, there is no limitation if you input **0**, thus"
" allowing any number of user to self-register.\n"
"If you input any other number, you will create a limitation on"
" self-registering users.\n"
"That means that as soon as the limit is reached, users cannot self-register"
" but they can still be registered by the *admin* user.\n"
"Using the value **1**, disables the self-registration since the spot is used"
" by the *admin* user.\n"
msgstr ""

