#: en/./admins/04_Updating.md:31
msgid ""
"Updating to a new version from a zip archive is always an option. Begin by "
"unzipping the archive into your FreshRSS directory, overwriting old files, "
"remove `./data/do-install.txt`, and finally re-set group read (and write, if "
"you wish) permissions on all files in `.` and group write permissions on `./"
"data/`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:4
msgid ""
"This tutorial demonstrates commands for backing up FreshRSS. It assumes that "
"your main FreshRSS directory is `/usr/share/FreshRSS`; If you've installed "
"it somewhere else, substitute your path as necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation Backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:8
msgid "Do this before an upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a Backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:12
msgid ""
"First, Enter the directory you wish to save your backup to. Here, for "
"example, we'll save the backup to the user home directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cd ~\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:17
msgid ""
"Next, we'll create a gzipped tar archive of the FreshRSS directory. The "
"following command will archive the entire contents of your FreshRSS "
"installation in it's current state."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"tar -czf FreshRSS-backup.tgz -C /usr/share/FreshRSS/ .\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:22
msgid "And you're done!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Restoring from a Backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:26
msgid "First, copy the backup previously made into your FreshRSS directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cp ~/FreshRSS-backup.tgz /usr/share/FreshRSS/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:31
msgid "Next, change to your FreshRSS directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:31 en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:12
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cd /usr/share/FreshRSS/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:36
msgid "Extract the backup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"tar -xzf FreshRSS-backup.tgz\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:41
msgid ""
"And optionally, as cleanup, remove the copy of your backup from the FreshRSS "
"directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rm FreshRSS-backup.tgz\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "Backing up Feeds"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Feed list Export"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:49
msgid ""
"You can export your feed list in OPML format either from the web interface, "
"or from the [Command-Line Interface](https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/"
"blob/master/cli/README.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Saving Articles"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To save articles, you can use [phpMyAdmin](https://www.phpmyadmin.net/) or"
" MySQL tools, where `<db_user>` is your database username, `<db_host>` is the"
" hostname of your web server containing your FreshRSS database, and `<"
"freshrss_db>` is the database used by FreshRSS:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Backup.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysqldump --skip-comments --disable-keys --user=<db_user> --password --host <"
"db_host> --result-file=freshrss.dump.sql --databases <freshrss_db>\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring the email address validation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:5
msgid ""
"FreshRSS can verify that users give a valid email address. It is not "
"configured by default so you'll have to follow these few steps to verify "
"email addresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:8
msgid ""
"It is intended to administrators who host users and want to be sure to be "
"able to contact them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Force email validation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:14
msgid ""
"In your `data/config.php` file, you'll find a `force_email_validation` item: "
"set it to `true`. An email field now appears on the registration page and "
"emails are sent when users change their email."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can also enable this feature directly in FreshRSS: `Administration` >\n"
"`System configuration` > check `Force email addresses validation`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure the SMTP server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:24
msgid ""
"By default, FreshRSS will attempt to send emails with the [`mail`](https://"
"www.php.net/manual/en/function.mail.php)  function of PHP. It is the simpler "
"solution but it might not work as expected.  For example, we don't support "
"(yet?) sending emails from inside our official Docker images. We recommend "
"to use a proper SMTP server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:26
msgid ""
"To configure a SMTP server, you'll have to modify the `data/config.php` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:28
msgid ""
"First, change the `mailer` item to `smtp` (instead of the default `mail`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:34
msgid ""
"Then, you should change the `smtp` options like you would do with a regular "
"email client. You can find the full list of options in the [`config.default."
"php` file](/config.default.php).  If you're not sure to what each item is "
"corresponding, you may find useful [the PHPMailer documentation](http://"
"phpmailer.github.io/PHPMailer/classes/PHPMailer.PHPMailer.PHPMailer."
"html#properties)  (which is used by FreshRSS under the hood)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Check your SMTP server is correctly configured"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/05_Configuring_email_validation.md:40
msgid ""
"To do so, once you've enabled the `force_email_validation` option, you only "
