#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation on Debian 9/Ubuntu 16.04"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:4
msgid ""
"This tutorial will give you step-by-step commands to install the latest "
"stable release of FreshRSS with Apache and MySQL using git. It's always "
"recommended that you [backup your installation](05_Backup.md) before updating"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:6
msgid ""
"Please note: Commands need to be run as an administrator; either perform the "
"following from a sudo shell (`sudo -s`) or use an administrator account."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Part 1: Setting up and configuring the LAMP stack"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:9
msgid ""
"Begin by installing Apache, and enable Apache modules needed for FreshRSS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"apt install apache2\n"
"\n"
"a2enmod headers expires rewrite ssl\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:15
msgid ""
"Then, you have to configure Apache. You can create a file in `/etc/apache2/"
"sites-available`, based on [our example configuration file](10_ServerConfig."
"md). Once you're done, create a symbolic link from this file to the `sites-"
"enabled` folder:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ln -s /etc/apache2/sites-available/freshrss.conf"
" /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/freshrss.conf\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:21
msgid "Next, install PHP and the necessary modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"apt install php php-curl php-gmp php-intl php-mbstring php-sqlite3 php-xml"
" php-zip\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:26
msgid "Install the PHP module for Apache"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"apt install libapache2-mod-php\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:31
msgid ""
"Next, we'll need to install and configure MySQL. Install MySQL components "
"like so:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo apt install mysql-server mysql-client php-mysql\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:36
msgid "MySQL must now be started:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"service mysql-server start\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:42
msgid ""
"We'll need to configure MySQL.  **Note:** As you've just installed mysql, "
"there will be no root password; simply hit enter on the first step"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql_secure_installation\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:47
msgid "And restart it"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"service mysql-server restart\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:52
msgid "Finally, restart MySQL and the web server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"\n"
"service apache2 restart\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Part 2: Installing FreshRSS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:60
msgid "Begin by installing git, if you don't already have it installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"apt install git\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:65
msgid "Next, change to the install directory and download FreshRSS using git"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cd /usr/share/\n"
"\n"
"git clone https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS.git\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:71
msgid ""
"Change to the new FreshRSS directory, and set the permissions so that your "
"Web server can access the files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:71
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cd FreshRSS\n"
"\n"
"chown -R :www-data .\n"
"\n"
"sudo chmod -R g+r .\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:77
msgid "We'll also need to allow the data folder to be written to, like so:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:77
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"chmod -R g+w ./data/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:82
msgid ""
"Optional: If you would like to allow updates from the Web interface, set "
"write permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"chmod -R g+w .\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:87
msgid "Finally, symlink the public folder to the root of your web directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:87
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ln -s /usr/share/FreshRSS/p /var/www/html/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "Part 3: Creating a Database for FreshRSS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Start a MySQL session. running this command will ask you for the MySQL"
" password you set earler, and then put you into a prompt that should look"
" like `MariaDB [(none)]>`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql -u root -p\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"From the MySQL prompt (`MariaDB [(none)]>`), run the following commands,"
" substituting `<username>`, `<password>`, and `<database_name>` for real"
" values.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"CREATE USER '<username>'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY '<password>';\n"
"\n"
"CREATE DATABASE `databaseName`;\n"
"\n"
"GRANT ALL privileges ON `databaseName`.* TO 'userName'@localhost;\n"
"\n"
"FLUSH PRIVILEGES;\n"
"\n"
"QUIT;\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:112
msgid ""
"A brief explanation of the previous command block: * You first create a "
"database user for FreshRSS to use.  * Then you create a database for "
"FreshRSS to store data in.  * You grant permissions for the user you created "
"to read, write, and modify the database.  * Flushing privileges reloads the "
"permissions, which makes the previous command take effect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "Part 4: Finishing the Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/06_LinuxInstall.md:116
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can now finish the installation from a web browser by navigating to to"
" `http://<your_server>/p` and following the graphical prompts.\n"
"Alternatively, you can finish the installation using [the"
" cli](https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/tree/master/cli)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Updating on Debian 9/Ubuntu 16.04"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:4
msgid ""
"This tutorial demonstrates commands for updating FreshRSS. It assumes that "
"your main FreshRSS directory is `/usr/share/FreshRSS`; If you've installed "
"it somewhere else, substitute your path as necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using git"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**You must have used git to install FreshRSS to use this update method.**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:10 en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:70
msgid ""
"If your local user doesn't have write access to the FreshRSS folder, use a "
"sudo shell (`sudo -s`), prefix the following commands with `sudo `, or "
"switch to an account that does have write access to the folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:12 en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:72
msgid "Change to your FreshRSS directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:17
msgid ""
"Verify the branch you're currently on. For stable releases, this should be "
"`master`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"git branch\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:23
msgid "Fetch the most recent code from the FreshRSS github Page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"git fetch --all\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:28
msgid ""
"Note: If you wish to switch to a specific version of FreshRSS, or switch to/"
"from the dev branch, this is the time to do that. Example commands for "
"switching branches are found below, in \"Switching Branches\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:30
msgid "Check for an update"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"git status\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:35
msgid ""
"If there's not an update, you're done! If there is, continue the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:37
msgid "Discard manual changes and delete manual additions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"get reset --hard\n"
"\n"
"git clean -f -d\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '6. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:43
msgid "Delete the file that triggers the install wizard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rm data/do-install.txt\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '7. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:48
msgid "Update to the new version of FreshRSS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"git pull\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '8. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:53
msgid "Re-set correct permissions so that your web server can access the files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:53 en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"chown -R :www-data . && chmod -R g+r . && chmod -R g+w ./data/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Switching Branches"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:60
msgid ""
"Any command listed here should be run between steps 3 and 4 in the previous "
"section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:62
msgid ""
"To switch from stable to dev (if you haven't before) use the following "
"command: `git checkout -b dev origin/dev`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:64
msgid ""
"If you've checked out dev and want to go back to master, the command would "
"be `git checkout master`. After the first time you check out the dev branch, "
"you can use this syntax to switch between the two main branches at will."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you wish to switch to [a specific release of"
" FreshRSS](https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/releases), you would use the"
" command `git checkout <release_name>`, where <release_name> is the specific"
" release number you wish to check out (for example, `git checkout 1.12.0`)."
" Be aware that checking out a specific release will leave you in a state"
" where you can't automatically update; you'll need to run `git checkout"
" master` or `git checkout dev` before you'll be able to pull updates from git"
" automatically.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using the zip Archive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:77
msgid "Download and unzip the update file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:77
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"wget https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS/archive/master.zip\n"
"\n"
"unzip master.zip\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:83
msgid "Overwrite all your existing files with the new ones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cp -R FreshRSS-master/* .\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:88
msgid "Re-set permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:93
msgid ""
"Clean up the FreshRSS directory by deleting the downloaded zip, the file "
"forcing the setup wizard and the temporary directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/07_LinuxUpdate.md:93
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rm -f master.zip\n"
"\n"
"rm -f data/do-install.txt\n"
"\n"
"rm -rf FreshRSS-master/\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting Up Automatic Feed Updating"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:4
msgid ""
"FreshRSS updating is controlled by a script located at `./app/"
"actualize_script.php`. Knowing this, we can create a Cron job to launch the "
"update script."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:6
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** the update script will not fetch feeds more often than every twenty"
" minutes, so there's no sense in setting the Cron job to run anymore often"
" than that.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:8
msgid ""
"You will need to check the Cron documentation for your specific distribution "
"([Debian/Ubuntu](https://help.ubuntu.com/community/CronHowto), [Red Hat/"
"Fedora/CentOS](https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Administration_Guide_Draft/"
"Cron), [Slackware](https://docs.slackware.com/fr:slackbook:process_control?"
"#cron), [Gentoo](https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Cron), [Arch Linux](https://"
"wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Cron)...) to insure you set the Cron job "
"correctly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:10
msgid ""
"It's advisable that you run the Cron job as your Web server user (often `www-"
"data`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example on Debian/Ubuntu"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:13
msgid "To run the updater script every hour, and 10 minutes past the hour:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:15
msgid "Run `sudo crontab -e` and copy the following line into the crontab:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"10 * * * * www-data php -f /usr/share/FreshRSS/app/actualize_script.php >"
" /tmp/FreshRSS.log 2>&1\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/08_FeedUpdates.md:19
msgid ""
"This crontab example, of course, assumes that FreshRSS is installed in `/usr/"
"share/FreshRSS`; if you've installed it somewhere else, be sure to correct "
"the path in your crontab entry."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Access Control"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:4
msgid ""
"FreshRSS offers three methods of Access control: Form Authentication using "
"Javascript, HTTP based Authentication, or an uncontrolled state with no "
"authentication required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Form Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:8
msgid ""
"Form Authentication requires the use of Javascript. It will work on any "
"supported version of PHP, but version 5.5 or newer is recommended (see "
"footnote 1 in [prerequisites](02_Prerequisites.md) for the reason why)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:10
msgid ""
"This option requires nothing more than selecting Form Authentication during "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "HTTP Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:14
msgid ""
"You may also choose to use HTTP Authentication provided by your web server."
"[^1]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:16
msgid ""
"If you choose to use this option, create a `./p/i/.htaccess` file with a "
"matching `.htpasswd` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "No Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:19
msgid ""
"Not using authentication on your server is dangerous, as anyone with access "
"to your server would be able to make changes as an admin. It is never "
"advisable to not use any form of authentication, but **never** chose this "
"option on a server that is able to be accessed outside of your home network."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hints"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:23
msgid ""
"You can switch your authentication method at any time by editing the `./data/"
"config.php` file, on the line that begins `'auth_type'`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./admins/09_AccessControl.md:24
msgid ""
"[^1]: See [the Apache documentation](https://httpd.apache.org/docs/trunk/"
"howto/auth.html)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
