#, no-wrap
msgid "Permissions under SELinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./users/07_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:51
msgid ""
"Some Linux distribution like Fedora or RedHat Enterprise Linux have SELinux "
"system enabled. This acts like a firewall application, so all applications "
"cannot write/modify files under certain conditions. While installing "
"FreshRSS, step 2 can fail if the httpd process cannot write to some data sub-"
"directories, the following command should be executed as root :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/./users/07_Frequently_Asked_Questions.md:51
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"semanage fcontext -a -t httpd_sys_rw_content_t"
" '/usr/share/FreshRSS/data(/.*)?'\n"
"\n"
"restorecon -Rv /usr/share/FreshRSS/data\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

